SIMPLE: uncreated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uncreated
<hw>Un`cre*at"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[In sense 1, properly p. p. of
<ets>uncreate</ets>; in senses 2 and 3, pref. <ets>un-</ets> not +
<ets>created</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Deprived of existence;
annihilated.</def> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not yet created; <as>as, misery
<ex>uncreated</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not existing by creation; self-existent; eternal;
<as>as, God is an <ex>uncreated</ex> being</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncreatedness</ent>⟦br⟧
